"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102058","Home Office","false","2014-11-11","<p>Following the commitment made during the passage of the Data Retention and Investigatory Powers Act 2014, legislation to establish an Independent Privacy and Civil Liberties Board will be brought forward shortly.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-11-11T15:54:50.3170142Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102058/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102058/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102058/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-31","Independent Privacy and Civil Liberties Board","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she plans to bring forward proposals for the creation of the Independent Privacy and Civil Liberties Board.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","212793"
