"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102063","Prime Minister","false","2014-11-05","<p>Details of my meetings are available on the gov.uk website.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2014-11-05T14:50:07.1230226Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102063/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102063/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102063/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2014-10-31","Culture, Practices and Ethics of the Press Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, when he last met (a) Andy Coulson, (b) Rebekah Brooks, (c) Rupert Murdoch and (d) Trevor Kavanagh; what the purpose of each such meeting was; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","212835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102064","Home Office","false","2014-11-25","<p>The report of the Panel Inquiry into Child Sexual Abuse will be shared with the Home Office before it is published.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-11-25T14:37:43.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102064/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102064/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102064/answer","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102064/answer/previousversion/26314","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-31","Offences against Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the report of the Government's inquiry into historic child abuse will be shared with her Department before it is published.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","212838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102065","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-06","<p>Enforcement of legislation including punishment of offenders is a matter for the Home Office. The police decide whether an offence may be being committed and take such action as they consider appropriate in each case. Action might range from informal advice to, for specified offences, the offer of a fixed penalty, to prosecution.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-11-06T09:59:26.7423638Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102065/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102065/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102065/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-10-31","Motorcycles: Noise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 23 October 2014 to Question 211087, what current legal mechanisms are in place to tackle excessive motorcycle noise and punish the owners of such vehicles.","false","Biography information for Eric Ollerenshaw","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Eric Ollerenshaw","212806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102066","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-07","<p>We have rigorous checks built into the service, which help to detect, deter and remedy inappropriate use of the site. When we identify a duplicate job, we remove it.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-11-07T14:05:34.0426996Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102066/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102066/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102066/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-31","Vacancies: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent estimate he has made of the number of duplicate job postings on the Universal Jobmatch website.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","212796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102067","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-07","<p /> <p>(a)We have rigorous checks built into the service, which help to detect, deter and remedy inappropriate use of the site. When we identify a duplicate job, we remove it.</p><p>(b) When an employer posts a job they set an expiry date which they can change at any time or close the job earlier when it is filled. However, to maintain the system, the UJ service will automatically set an expiry date of 60 days.</p><p> </p><p>However, if we are informed that a job is no longer available we will investigate and ensure the vacancy is expired if appropriate. This can be done by using the 'Contact Us' facility within Universal Jobmatch.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-11-07T14:09:56.1516595Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102067/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102067/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102067/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-31","Vacancies: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department is taking to reduce the number of (a) duplicate and (b) expired job postings on the Universal Jobmatch website.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","212797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102068","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-17","<p>Over the next few months HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) will be migrating its existing telephone services to a new telephony platform. This will improve the way that the queuing systems work and, over time, will lead to reduced wait times.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC is also looking at a number of initiatives to improve customer service and wait times. These include: greater flexible working across HMRC to improve its response to particular peaks in demand; and investing in online and digital services for the future, opening up a wider variety of channels.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All HMRC helplines, including those for Tax Credit Helpline are landline numbers.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","212842","2014-11-17T15:52:57.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102068/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102068/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102068/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-31","Welfare Tax Credits: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to reduce the length of time taken to answer calls to tax credit helplines.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","212822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102069","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-07","<p /> <p>The FAS may pay members of schemes which transfer their assets to government a tax-free lump sum when payments begin, provided their scheme has not paid them during the winding up period. In the three months from January to March 2010, 263 such members were paid a scheme pension and did not receive a tax-free lump sum.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-11-07T12:33:14.7876456Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102069/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102069/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102069/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-31","Pensions: Financial Assistance Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will estimate the number of members of pension schemes who did not receive a tax-free lump sum on receipt of pension in the few months prior to the Financial Assistance Scheme (FAS) regulations adopted in April 2010, which allowed members who were not already in receipt of pension payments to give up some of their FAS assistance for a lump sum payment on transfer of the scheme to FAS.","false","Biography information for Sandra Osborne","Ayr, Carrick and Cumnock","Sandra Osborne","212827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102070","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-05","<p /> <p>(a) Whilst Jobcentres remain the branding of the Department's frontline face to face service, the executive agency status of Jobcentre Plus ended during 2011-12 as DWP integrated its frontline agencies into one operation. DWP has a Whistleblowing policy which covers all employees. This encourages employees to raise any concerns about wrongdoing. Where an employee raises a concern under this policy, the procedures ensure that they are provided with protection, help and support.</p><p> </p><p>(b) Responsibility for the protection of whistleblowers in Work Programme providers rests with their employers. Employers are subject to the Public Interest Disclosure Act which protects whistleblowers from suffering any detriment as a result of raising a genuine concern.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-11-05T14:42:39.6947261Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102070/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102070/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102070/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-31","Social Security Benefits: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what provisions are in place to protect whistleblowers in (a) Jobcentre Plus and (b) Work Programme providers.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","212845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102071","Cabinet Office","false","2014-11-05","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2014-11-05T15:16:12.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102071/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102071/answer","PQ 212846 ONS 382.pdf","PQ 212846 ONS 382.pdf","ONS Letter to Member - Jobseekers Allowance BME","ONS Letter to Member - Jobseekers Allowance BME","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102071/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-10-31","Jobseeker's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of those claiming jobseeker's allowance are BME.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","212846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102072","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-17","<p>Over the next few months HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) will be migrating its existing telephone services to a new telephony platform. This will improve the way that the queuing systems work and, over time, will lead to reduced wait times.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC is also looking at a number of initiatives to improve customer service and wait times. These include: greater flexible working across HMRC to improve its response to particular peaks in demand; and investing in online and digital services for the future, opening up a wider variety of channels.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All HMRC helplines, including those for Tax Credit Helpline are landline numbers.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","212822","2014-11-17T15:52:57.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102072/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102072/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/102072/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-31","Working Tax Credit: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will introduce landline telephone numbers for calls to HM Revenue and Customs' helplines for working tax credits queries.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","212842"
