"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101889","Department of Health","false","2014-11-06","There is currently no reliable data on the numbers of people who have contracted pneumococcal community acquired pneumonia. Data on cases of community acquired pneumonia who were managed in the community are not recorded.","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-11-06T17:35:12.2812494Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101889/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101889/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101889/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-30","Pneumonia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people aged (a) 0 to five, (b) six to 15, (c) 16 to 64 and (d) 65 and over contracted pneumococcal community-acquired pneumonia in each (i) NHS England local area team area and (ii) clinical commissioning group area in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Sir Bob Russell","Colchester","Sir Bob Russell","212758"
